This paper discusses the mathematical theory of machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The focus on algebraic expressions for subjective spatial and temporal patterns suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The discussion of subjective patterns also suggests that information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE) may be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the mention of a powerful tool for expressing patterns suggests that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
